# IMPORTANT: Environment Variables Setup

## DO NOT COMMIT THIS FILE TO VERSION CONTROL

Add `.env` to your `.gitignore` file to prevent exposing secrets.

## Required Environment Variables

### 1. Get your Stripe Publishable Key

1. Go to https://dashboard.stripe.com/test/apikeys
2. Copy your "Publishable key" (starts with `pk_test_`)
3. Replace `pk_test_YOUR_ACTUAL_KEY_HERE` below with your actual key

### 2. Update this file

```env
# Stripe Configuration
VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_YOUR_ACTUAL_KEY_HERE

# API Configuration  
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
```

### 3. Restart Vite Dev Server

After updating the `.env` file, you MUST restart your Vite development server for changes to take effect:

```bash
# Stop the server (Ctrl+C)
# Then restart:
npm run dev
```

## Backend Setup Required

The backend also needs Stripe configuration. Ensure `PFA/.env` contains:

```env
# Stripe Secret Key (from https://dashboard.stripe.com/test/apikeys)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_YOUR_SECRET_KEY

# Stripe Webhook Secret (from https://dashboard.stripe.com/test/webhooks)
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_YOUR_WEBHOOK_SECRET

# Database encryption key (generate a random string)
DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-random-encryption-key-here
```

## Security Notes

- ✅ Never commit `.env` files to version control
- ✅ Use test keys in development (`pk_test_` and `sk_test_`)
- ✅ Use production keys only in production environment
- ✅ Never expose secret keys (`sk_test_` or `sk_live_`) in frontend code
